Competere’s main activities consist in: 
- Producing research, analysis and studies on innovation and competition issues; 
- Providing support to its partners and fellows in understanding the political and economic scenario; 
- Building and managing public affairs, advocacy and communication campaigns on innovation and competition policies. 

In the pursuit of these activities, Competere operates with the following tools: 
- Outlook analysis, papers and blueprint documents on main public policies issues; 
- Editorial contents published in main newspapers and information outlets; 
- Meetings with members and staff of the European, international and national institutions; 
- Voluntary contribution to formal consultations at EU and national level; 
- Advocacy campaign on innovation and competition policies at EU, international and national level; 
- Communication activities.
